Governor John Bel Edwards
April 22 at 6:08 PM ·

Part of our new normal will mean wearing a mask or face-covering in public. Wearing a mask in public is just like holding a door open for someone, it's being kind and courteous, and it will be critical to Louisiana moving forward.

When I say mask, I mean wearing some sort of cloth facial covering. We've seen creative folks make masks out of t-shirts or other household materials, and I am encouraging everyone to begin the process now to start getting them for yourselves and your families.

Take this time to make sure you and everyone in your family has a face covering, you can buy or make masks. Remember, unless you are a healthcare worker, you do not need to wear or purchase N95 or surgical masks. #lagov #MaskUpLa

post_text:
Effective Immediately:

Due to the unknown future of sales tax funds that provide for the operation of this facility, the West Feliciana Parish Recycle Center will be temporarily closed.

Waste Management will continue their normal residential pickup and items may be placed for pick up by Waste Management on your normal pick up day.

As you place waste out for pickup, please keep the following in mind:
• All waste containers may not exceed 35 gallons.
•There may be a total of 6 containers/bags/bundles for each household on each pickup day. If more than this, it may take Waste Management a couple of pickups to get everything.
•Bulky waste may not exceed 2 cubic yards and will be picked up once a month.

We appreciate your understanding in this matter.

post_text:
There is a fake website with a Coronavirus map lurking on the Internet. If you are doing a random search for this topic, anyone could mistake this malicious website to be the real thing.

If you mistakenly go to the website, this fake Coronavirus Map will install a malware (program). This program (AZORult trojan) will infect your device with an application that will steal your information from a variety of sensitive data on your device. This program can spread via infected email attachments, online advertisements and social engineering.

Recommendations:
Be aware when navigating to websites. Misspellings are often key. Your anti-virus should remain up-to-date.

The parish is experiencing widespread power outages so please be aware of utility crews as they work to restore power.
We appreciate the cooperation we received with the curfew that allowed emergency workers to focus on those tasks necessary to keep the parish safe.

post_text:
Key things to remember:

- Be sure to turn the generator off and let it cool down before refueling.

- Never try to power the house wiring by plugging the generator into a wall outlet. Plug appliances directly into the generator, or use a heavy duty, outdoor-rated extension cord that is rated (in watts or amps) at least equal to the sum of the connected appliance loads.

- Generators should not be used indoors or any partially enclosed area and should be kept away from doors, windows and vents that could allow carbon monoxide to come indoors.

shared_text:
West Feliciana Parish Emergency Operations Center
July 13, 2019 at 4:07 PM ·

WEST FELICIANA PARISH UNDER MANDATORY CURFEW

Due to the extreme weather we’ve experienced today, and more of the same expected tonight, the Parish of West Feliciana and the Town of St. Francisville have instituted a curfew for tonight.
The mandatory curfew will go into effect at 8pm this evening through 6am tomorrow morning.
This curfew is being put into place to protect the public and allow first responders and other critical workforce members to do their jobs without the presence of sightseers on the roadways.
Only essential and critical workforce will be allowed on public streets.
If anyone is found to be violating this curfew during the slotted time, proper action will be taken against them.
Please follow this order and stay safe.

post_text:
Residents are encouraged to begin preparations for severe weather forecast through the weekend. Sandbags are available for residents to pick up at WFP Crisis Response Building (located next to the animal shelter) and at WFP Maintenance Facility.

Sandbags will continue to be made available at these locations as long as necessary. Due to high demand, residents may need to fill their own bags and are advised to bring a shovel for this purpose.

Drivers should avoid driving in adverse road conditions, unless necessary and are reminded to heed traffic advisories, obey traffic signs/detours and to exercise caution when driving in and around standing water.

For the most up-to-date information from your local officials, follow us and these pages on Facebook: West Feliciana Parish Emergency Operations Center & West Feliciana Parish Sheriff's Office

West Feliciana Parish Recycling Center is up & running!

Please remember to recycle right. Keep items loose and only place acceptable materials in compactor.

Recyclable items include plastic bottles, paper, metal cans, glass containers and flattened cardboard. Everything else should be reused, donated, composted or disposed of safely. A bulk waste bin is available on site for your convenience, as well as designated areas for appliances and tires. Hazardous materials are prohibited.
